This guy is somewhat interesting, because he makes it obvious that he's "lucid" and self-aware, but simultaneously also does believe whatever he jokes about, in spite of that. All irony is thin, but here that is made fully explicit. It's a "revelation of the method" for rhetoric.

Like the Roman actor who got baptized as part of a theatre play and rose as a ready martyr from the waters, the couple that "joked" about dating each other and calling themselves gf/bf, the ironic cult that is still a cult,  the unknowing participant in a dark occult ritual, etc.

As all cults have a threefold structure - outer layer knowing it a cult, middle seeing it as a "joke", inner knowing its true nature as cult, so Gene Wolfe's aliens wore masks of human faces, over a monstrous insectoid appearance, which was also a mask - human again underneath.
